---
import { ClientRouter } from "astro:transitions";
import "../../styles/global.css";
import ProjectDescription from "../../components/ProjectDescription";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <ClientRouter />
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Flashy - Simple flashcard app</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-foreground">
    <a
      href="/"
      class="fixed left-6 top-6 flex items-center gap-2 rounded-md border border-neutral-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm font-geist shadow-sm transition hover:shadow"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="16"
        height="16"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        class="lucide lucide-arrow-left-icon lucide-arrow-left"
        ><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"></path><path d="M19 12H5"></path></svg
      >
      <span>Return home</span>
    </a>
    <main
      class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-4xl flex-col gap-6 px-6 py-24 font-geist"
    >
      <h1
        class="text-3xl font-semibold md:text-5xl"
        transition:name="project-flashy"
      >
        Flashy - Simple flashcard app
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600">
        Full Stack App / May 2024
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-row items-center justify-start gap-4">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/hiiramsan/flashy-v2"
          target="_blank"
          class="inline-flex! items-center! gap-2! rounded-md border border-neutral-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm font-geist shadow-sm transition hover:shadow"
        >
          <span>Visit the Github</span>
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="16"
            height="16"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="lucide lucide-arrow-up-right-icon lucide-arrow-up-right shrink-0"
            ><path d="M7 7h10v10"></path><path d="M7 17 17 7"></path></svg
          >
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://flashy-v2.vercel.app/"
          target="_blank"
          class="inline-flex! items-center! gap-2! rounded-md border border-neutral-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm font-geist shadow-sm transition hover:shadow"
        >
          <span>Visit project</span>
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            width="16"
            height="16"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            class="lucide lucide-arrow-up-right-icon lucide-arrow-up-right shrink-0"
            ><path d="M7 7h10v10"></path><path d="M7 17 17 7"></path></svg
          >
        </a>
      </div>
      <img
        src="/images/flashy.png"
        alt="Project preview"
        class="w-150 rounded-md"
      />
      <ProjectDescription
        client:load
        version1={[
          "Flashy was built with Node, JavaScript, CSS, HTML, Express, and MongoDB. It was my first full stack project and the first app I actually used.",
          "I built it because I was paying for a flashcards app and wanted a free version that did the same job.",
          "It pushed me through the full flow: auth, CRUD, data models, and deployment.",
          "People close to me know this project is meaningful to me, even if I see its flaws now.",
        ]}
        version2={[
          "I am profoundly moved to reflect on the successful sunsetting of my initial venture into Full-Stack Architectural Engineering: the deployment of Flashy, a disruptive, vertically integrated Cognitive Retention Ecosystem.",
          "What began as a strategic initiative to optimize my personal financial runway by pivoting away from high-friction, subscription-based SaaS (Study-as-a-Service) models, evolved into a masterclass in End-to-End Product Lifecycle Management. By architecting a robust solution using the high-concurrency Node/Express/MongoDB stack, I successfully engineered a proprietary 'Knowledge-Persistence' engine that neutralized the market dominance of legacy competitors.",
          "This mission-critical project forced a deep-dive into the core pillars of enterprise software: implementing high-security Identity Management (Auth), establishing scalable Schema Design, and overseeing the rigorous Deployment Pipeline of my first truly production-ready asset. While I now view the initial MVP through a lens of Continuous Improvement and Iterative Refinement, the project remains a foundational milestone in my journey toward Technical Mastery.",
          "#FullStackVisionary #DisruptiveLearning #CognitiveArchitecture #SaaSKiller #FinancialOptimization #BuildInPublic #LegacyCode"
        ]}
      />
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
